 What We are Watching

 Theatre - Folklore and fantasy

 Ballavpurer Roopkatha

 Nandipat revives this Badal Sircar play under Prakash Bhattacharya?s direction. At the core of the comedy is Bhupati Ray and his decrepit palace that he wants to sell off. Once the buyer takes possession, Ray?s ancestral ghost residing in the house takes an interest in the young woman who has come to live here. The music is by Pankaj Munshi and off-stage voice by Soumitra Basu.

 Catch it at Rabindra Sadan, 6.30 pm, April 27

 Aasarer Ek Din

 The play revolves around the creative genius of Kalidasa and his muse, the beautiful Mallika. The poet leaves her to marry a princess but renounces everything some years later to be with his beloved. But the passage of time has taken a toll on everything around him, including his creativity. The play scripted by Mohan Rakesh will be staged by Durgadas Smrity Sangha. Directed by Tirthankar Chattopadhyay.

 Catch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 10 am, April 24




